experiences.description: Developed and maintained ETL pipelines for various clients in the finance and healthcare industries.  Implemented data quality checks and monitoring systems to ensure data accuracy and reliability.  Worked with large datasets to build data warehouses using cloud technologies like AWS Redshift and Snowflake.  Collaborated with data scientists to provide data solutions for machine learning projects. Designed and implemented data security measures to comply with industry regulations.

Led a team of data engineers in building a scalable data platform for a fast-growing AI startup.  Designed and implemented a real-time data ingestion pipeline using Kafka and Spark Streaming.  Developed data models and data governance policies to ensure data consistency and integrity.  Mentored junior data engineers and provided technical guidance. Worked closely with product managers to define data requirements and deliver data-driven solutions.

Architected and implemented a new data warehouse solution using cloud-native technologies.  Led the migration of existing data pipelines to the new platform.  Developed and maintained data pipelines for machine learning models used in fraud detection and risk assessment.  Provided technical leadership and mentorship to a team of data engineers.  Worked with cross-functional teams to define data strategy and implement data governance policies. Improved data pipeline efficiency by 30% by optimizing query performance and reducing data storage costs.

education.description: Graduated with honors.  Focused on data structures, algorithms, and database management systems. Participated in research projects related to data mining and machine learning.

Completed a Master's degree in Data Science with a focus on statistical modeling and machine learning.  Published research papers on data privacy and security. Developed a strong understanding of data ethics and responsible data practices.
